            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20can%20we%20explain%20God's%20choices%3F%20In%20John%2015%3A16%2C%20Jesus%20said%2C%20%22You%20didn't%20choose%20me.%20I%20chose%20you.%22%20Saul%20was%20the%20last%20person%20we%20would%20have%20expected%20God%20to%20select%20as%20an%20instrument%20to%20tell%20the%20world%20about%20Jesus.%20But%20we%20know%20from%201%20Corinthians%201%3A27%20that%20God%20deliberately%20chooses%20%22things%20the%20world%20considers%20foolish%20in%20order%20to%20shame%20those%20who%20think%20they%20are%20wise.%22%20In%20choosing%20Saul%20as%20a%20divine%20instrument%2C%20God%20certainly%20knew%20that%20his%20testimony%20would%20totally%20confound%20the%20Jews.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJeroboam%2C%20another%20of%20God's%20unlikely%20choices%2C%20was%20equally%20surprised%20when%20the%20prophet%20Ahijah%20informed%20him%20of%20his%20future%20destiny%20as%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20(1%20Kings%2011%3A29).%20In%20a%20moment%2C%20because%20of%20God's%20sovereign%20selection%2C%20the%20entire%20course%20of%20his%20life%20was%20altered.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20may%20never%20figure%20out%20the%20ways%20of%20God%20in%20laying%20His%20hand%20on%20seemingly%20unworthy%20vessels%20in%20order%20to%20glorify%20Himself.%20Yet%20if%20you%20are%20a%20Christian%2C%20you%20are%20chosen.%20If%20you%20are%20chosen%2C%20you%20are%20ordained.%20If%20you%20are%20ordained%2C%20you%20will%20produce%20fruit%20(John%2015%3A16).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERelax%2C%20and%20carry%20out%20your%20calling!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
