            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Kings.11:1-12:19",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Kings%2011%3A1-12%3A19%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESolomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Many%20Wives%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20King%20Solomon%20loved%20many%20foreign%20women.%20Besides%20Pharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughter%2C%20he%20married%20women%20from%20Moab%2C%20Ammon%2C%20Edom%2C%20Sidon%2C%20and%20from%20among%20the%20Hittites.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20clearly%20instructed%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20must%20not%20marry%20them%2C%20because%20they%20will%20turn%20your%20hearts%20to%20their%20gods.%26%23x201D%3B%20Yet%20Solomon%20insisted%20on%20loving%20them%20anyway.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20had%20700%26%23xA0%3Bwives%20of%20royal%20birth%20and%20300%26%23xA0%3Bconcubines.%20And%20in%20fact%2C%20they%20did%20turn%20his%20heart%20away%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20old%20age%2C%20they%20turned%20his%20heart%20to%20worship%20other%20gods%20instead%20of%20being%20completely%20faithful%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God%2C%20as%20his%20father%2C%20David%2C%20had%20been.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20worshiped%20Ashtoreth%2C%20the%20goddess%20of%20the%20Sidonians%2C%20and%20Molech%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EMilcom%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Molech%3B%20also%20in%2011%3A33.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20detestable%20god%20of%20the%20Ammonites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20this%20way%2C%20Solomon%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%3B%20he%20refused%20to%20follow%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20completely%2C%20as%20his%20father%2C%20David%2C%20had%20done.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20the%20Mount%20of%20Olives%2C%20east%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20mountain%20east%20of%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20he%20even%20built%20a%20pagan%20shrine%20for%20Chemosh%2C%20the%20detestable%20god%20of%20Moab%2C%20and%20another%20for%20Molech%2C%20the%20detestable%20god%20of%20the%20Ammonites.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20built%20such%20shrines%20for%20all%20his%20foreign%20wives%20to%20use%20for%20burning%20incense%20and%20sacrificing%20to%20their%20gods.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20very%20angry%20with%20Solomon%2C%20for%20his%20heart%20had%20turned%20away%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20who%20had%20appeared%20to%20him%20twice.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20had%20warned%20Solomon%20specifically%20about%20worshiping%20other%20gods%2C%20but%20Solomon%20did%20not%20listen%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20command.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20now%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BSince%20you%20have%20not%20kept%20my%20covenant%20and%20have%20disobeyed%20my%20decrees%2C%20I%20will%20surely%20tear%20the%20kingdom%20away%20from%20you%20and%20give%20it%20to%20one%20of%20your%20servants.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20your%20father%2C%20David%2C%20I%20will%20not%20do%20this%20while%20you%20are%20still%20alive.%20I%20will%20take%20the%20kingdom%20away%20from%20your%20son.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20even%20so%2C%20I%20will%20not%20take%20away%20the%20entire%20kingdom%3B%20I%20will%20let%20him%20be%20king%20of%20one%20tribe%2C%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20my%20servant%20David%20and%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20my%20chosen%20city.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESolomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Adversaries%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20raised%20up%20Hadad%20the%20Edomite%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Edom%26%23x2019%3Bs%20royal%20family%2C%20to%20be%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20adversary.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EYears%20before%2C%20David%20had%20defeated%20Edom.%20Joab%2C%20his%20army%20commander%2C%20had%20stayed%20to%20bury%20some%20of%20the%20Israelite%20soldiers%20who%20had%20died%20in%20battle.%20While%20there%2C%20they%20killed%20every%20male%20in%20Edom.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EJoab%20and%20the%20army%20of%20Israel%20had%20stayed%20there%20for%20six%20months%2C%20killing%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Hadad%20and%20a%20few%20of%20his%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20royal%20officials%20escaped%20and%20headed%20for%20Egypt.%20(Hadad%20was%20just%20a%20boy%20at%20the%20time.)%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20set%20out%20from%20Midian%20and%20went%20to%20Paran%2C%20where%20others%20joined%20them.%20Then%20they%20traveled%20to%20Egypt%20and%20went%20to%20Pharaoh%2C%20who%20gave%20them%20a%20home%2C%20food%2C%20and%20some%20land.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EPharaoh%20grew%20very%20fond%20of%20Hadad%2C%20and%20he%20gave%20him%20his%20wife%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sister%20in%20marriage%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20sister%20of%20Queen%20Tahpenes.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EShe%20bore%20him%20a%20son%20named%20Genubath.%20Tahpenes%20raised%20him%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Eweaned%20him.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20Pharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20palace%20among%20Pharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20own%20sons.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_21%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20news%20reached%20Hadad%20in%20Egypt%20that%20David%20and%20his%20commander%20Joab%20were%20both%20dead%2C%20he%20said%20to%20Pharaoh%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLet%20me%20return%20to%20my%20own%20country.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_22%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhy%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Pharaoh%20asked%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20do%20you%20lack%20here%20that%20makes%20you%20want%20to%20go%20home%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BNothing%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20replied.%20%26%23x201C%3BBut%20even%20so%2C%20please%20let%20me%20return%20home.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_23%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EGod%20also%20raised%20up%20Rezon%20son%20of%20Eliada%20as%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20adversary.%20Rezon%20had%20fled%20from%20his%20master%2C%20King%20Hadadezer%20of%20Zobah%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_24%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20had%20become%20the%20leader%20of%20a%20gang%20of%20rebels.%20After%20David%20conquered%20Hadadezer%2C%20Rezon%20and%20his%20men%20fled%20to%20Damascus%2C%20where%20he%20became%20king.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_25%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3ERezon%20was%20Israel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20bitter%20adversary%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20and%20he%20made%20trouble%2C%20just%20as%20Hadad%20did.%20Rezon%20hated%20Israel%20intensely%20and%20continued%20to%20reign%20in%20Aram.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_26%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJeroboam%20Rebels%20against%20Solomon%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EAnother%20rebel%20leader%20was%20Jeroboam%20son%20of%20Nebat%2C%20one%20of%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20own%20officials.%20He%20came%20from%20the%20town%20of%20Zeredah%20in%20Ephraim%2C%20and%20his%20mother%20was%20Zeruah%2C%20a%20widow.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_27%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20story%20behind%20his%20rebellion.%20Solomon%20was%20rebuilding%20the%20supporting%20terraces%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A27%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20millo.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20repairing%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20city%20of%20his%20father%2C%20David.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_28%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EJeroboam%20was%20a%20very%20capable%20young%20man%2C%20and%20when%20Solomon%20saw%20how%20industrious%20he%20was%2C%20he%20put%20him%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20labor%20force%20from%20the%20tribes%20of%20Ephraim%20and%20Manasseh%2C%20the%20descendants%20of%20Joseph.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_29%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20as%20Jeroboam%20was%20leaving%20Jerusalem%2C%20the%20prophet%20Ahijah%20from%20Shiloh%20met%20him%20along%20the%20way.%20Ahijah%20was%20wearing%20a%20new%20cloak.%20The%20two%20of%20them%20were%20alone%20in%20a%20field%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_30%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20Ahijah%20took%20hold%20of%20the%20new%20cloak%20he%20was%20wearing%20and%20tore%20it%20into%20twelve%20pieces.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_31%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20said%20to%20Jeroboam%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTake%20ten%20of%20these%20pieces%2C%20for%20this%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20says%3A%20%26%23x2018%3BI%20am%20about%20to%20tear%20the%20kingdom%20from%20the%20hand%20of%20Solomon%2C%20and%20I%20will%20give%20ten%20of%20the%20tribes%20to%20you!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_32%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20I%20will%20leave%20him%20one%20tribe%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20my%20servant%20David%20and%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20which%20I%20have%20chosen%20out%20of%20all%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_33%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20Solomon%20has%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A33%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%2C%20Syriac%2C%20and%20Latin%20Vulgate%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EFor%20they%20have.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20abandoned%20me%20and%20worshiped%20Ashtoreth%2C%20the%20goddess%20of%20the%20Sidonians%3B%20Chemosh%2C%20the%20god%20of%20Moab%3B%20and%20Molech%2C%20the%20god%20of%20the%20Ammonites.%20He%20has%20not%20followed%20my%20ways%20and%20done%20what%20is%20pleasing%20in%20my%20sight.%20He%20has%20not%20obeyed%20my%20decrees%20and%20regulations%20as%20David%20his%20father%20did.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_34%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3B%26%23x2018%3BBut%20I%20will%20not%20take%20the%20entire%20kingdom%20from%20Solomon%20at%20this%20time.%20For%20the%20sake%20of%20my%20servant%20David%2C%20the%20one%20whom%20I%20chose%20and%20who%20obeyed%20my%20commands%20and%20decrees%2C%20I%20will%20keep%20Solomon%20as%20leader%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_35%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20I%20will%20take%20the%20kingdom%20away%20from%20his%20son%20and%20give%20ten%20of%20the%20tribes%20to%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_36%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2236%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3EHis%20son%20will%20have%20one%20tribe%20so%20that%20the%20descendants%20of%20David%20my%20servant%20will%20continue%20to%20reign%2C%20shining%20like%20a%20lamp%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20the%20city%20I%20have%20chosen%20to%20be%20the%20place%20for%20my%20name.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_37%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2237%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E37%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20I%20will%20place%20you%20on%20the%20throne%20of%20Israel%2C%20and%20you%20will%20rule%20over%20all%20that%20your%20heart%20desires.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_38%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2238%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E38%3C%2Fspan%3EIf%20you%20listen%20to%20what%20I%20tell%20you%20and%20follow%20my%20ways%20and%20do%20whatever%20I%20consider%20to%20be%20right%2C%20and%20if%20you%20obey%20my%20decrees%20and%20commands%2C%20as%20my%20servant%20David%20did%2C%20then%20I%20will%20always%20be%20with%20you.%20I%20will%20establish%20an%20enduring%20dynasty%20for%20you%20as%20I%20did%20for%20David%2C%20and%20I%20will%20give%20Israel%20to%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_39%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2239%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E39%3C%2Fspan%3EBecause%20of%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sin%20I%20will%20punish%20the%20descendants%20of%20David%26%23x2014%3Bthough%20not%20forever.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_11_40%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2240%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E40%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20tried%20to%20kill%20Jeroboam%2C%20but%20he%20fled%20to%20King%20Shishak%20of%20Egypt%20and%20stayed%20there%20until%20Sol